          0.8890980392156863
        ],
        "order": 39
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_46",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The best thing I can say about \"Shifting Gears,\" ABC's new Tim Allen- rants-about-woke-stuff-he-hates sit- com, is that I thought it would be a lot worse than it is.",
        "bbox": [
          0.2824242424242424,
          0.756078431372549,
          0.49333333333333335,
          0.7912156862745098
        ],
        "order": 41
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_38",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Libra (Sept.23-Oct. 23). Discussing the past? Conversations encourage you to reconnect with your heritage as Mercury enters Capricorn.",
        "bbox": [
          0.04424242424242424,
          0.7808627450980392,
          0.25272727272727274,
          0.8090980392156862
        ],
        "order": 42
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_47",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Yes, eight years after the network canceled his last sitcom of the same genre, \"Last Man Standing\" (later picked up by Fox, where it ran until 2021), Allen is back on ABC. And now, instead of playing an overwrought pa- triarch working at an outdoorsy com- pany battling with a wife and daugh- ters, he's an overwrought patriarch who owns a classic car shop and bat- tles one daughter, played by Kat Den- nings. So different!",
        "bbox": [
          0.283030303030303,
          0.791843137254902,
          0.49272727272727274,
          0.8762352941176471
        ],
        "order": 43
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_39",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Scorpio (Oct. 24-Nov. 21). Getting to the point? You're not one to mince words as Mercury enters Capricorn. Straightforward speech sets the tone.",
        "bbox": [
          0.04424242424242424,
          0.8128627450980392,
          0.24787878787878787,
          0.8410980392156863
        ],
        "order": 44
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_40",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Sagittarius (Nov. 22-Dec. 21). Mercu- ry's three-week stint in Capricorn is the perfect time to get your affairs in order!",
        "bbox": [
          0.04363636363636364,
          0.8445490196078431,
          0.24727272727272728,
          0.8727843137254901
        ],
        "order": 45
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_41",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Capricorn (Dec. 22-Jan. 19). Feeling chatty? Methodical communication is your strong suit over the next three weeks.",
        "bbox": [
          0.04424242424242424,
          0.8765490196078431,
          0.24484848484848484,
          0.9047843137254902
        ],
        "order": 46
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_48",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "\"Gears\" (Wednesdays, 8 EsT/PST, ★★☆☆), created by Mike Scully and Julie Thacker-Scully (\"The Simp- sons\"), is neither original nor exciting; It's an unchallenging and not very fun- ny package of generational stereo- types and grating banter between Al- len and Dennings. The two episodes made available for review feature dia- logue so bland it could have been writ- ten by AI. They lack excitement in any way, but are not so achingly terrible they offend the senses. And consider-",
        "bbox": [
          0.283030303030303,
          0.8768627450980392,
          0.49272727272727274,
          0.9690980392156863
        ],
        "order": 47
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_21",
        "observed_type": "image_caption",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Tim Allen is Matt, a widower and owner of a classic car restoration shop, who gets a brave new reality when his daughter Riley (Kat Dennings) is forced to move back home with her two kids. PRoViDED BY MiKE TAING/DIsNEY",
        "bbox": [
          0.5054545454545455,
          0.8909803921568628,
          0.9290909090909091,
          0.9123137254901961
        ],
        "order": 48
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_42",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Aquarius (Jan. 20-Feb. 18). Fantasy meets reality as Mercury enters Cap- ricorn. A wild idea may be more achievable than you think.",
        "bbox": [
          0.04424242424242424,
          0.9085490196078432,
          0.24484848484848484,
          0.9370980392156862
        ],
        "order": 49
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_50",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "ing both Allen's track record and the re- cent spate of deeply disappointing mul- ti-camera sitcoms on broadcast TV, that's actually an achievement. Expec- tations are everything.",
        "bbox": [
          0.5066666666666667,
          0.9261176470588235,
          0.723030303030303,
          0.9618823529411765
        ],
        "order": 50
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_51",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "ower, everyman and possessor of Fox News opinions. His quiet life is turned upside down (a sitcom must) when his daughter Riley (Dennings) moves back",
        "bbox": [
          0.7375757575757576,
          0.9264313725490196,
          0.9545454545454546,
          0.9556078431372549
        ],
        "order": 51
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_43",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Pisces (Feb. 19-March 20). You commit to a venture for the long haul as Mer- cury enters Capricorn. Pool your re- sources.",
        "bbox": [
          0.04424242424242424,
          0.9405490196078431,
          0.25272727272727274,
          0.9690980392156863
        ],
        "order": 52
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_52",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "This series fi nds Allen as Matt, a wid",
        "bbox": [
          0.52,
          0.9621960784313726,
          0.7193939393939394,
          0.9694117647058823
        ],
        "order": 53
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_USAToday-2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_53",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "See SHIFTING GEARS, Page 2D",
        "bbox": [
